Apology</span><hr size=1> Already because of this misunderstanding, i've been deguilded from the guild i love, kos to AD, and friends from my guild wont even talk to me.  You all deserve an explanation, and i'll do my best to cover everything.<br>
<br>
There are two people that play my account and that is myself, and my good friend Sean.  Since it is my account and my character, whenever he is playing he asks me for advice on what to do and i make the decisions.  During the AD war, he would log on to PVP because he had never been in a war before.  Those that know me in AD can testify that i would never spam &quot;GOOM GOOM GOOM&quot; a thousand times in a row.  <br>
<br>
It was during this time that Alejos and Voltaar had their incident with Moehx.  For some reason, Sean felt he should email a gm and try and prove that they didnt do it.  He got an email back.  And he posted it under my name on the wudan message board.  Even the style of the email always seemed false to me at the time but i thought nothing of it.  Wudan officers, begged everyone not to do anything about the letter before they could verify that it was true.  They could never verify it and neither could I. <br>
<br>
Sean claims that he did not make the email up.  But therein remains the question of who did if he didnt?  Even I cant come up with any suggestions on that.  I decided to take the blame for this because him being on my account is my responsibility.  The totens had absolutely no idea that the email was false, and therefore they are innocent.  <br>
<br>
Of all the people this incident hurts me the most.  Right now i am kos to AD, it seems, and you have every reason to continue to do so.  However, Sean no longer has access, and the totens have already apologized.  This is my apology and i hope you accept it.   I am sorry for being responsible for the Gm letter that is indeed false.  <br>
<br>
